            <header>
             <h2 class="entry-title">
              <a href="/our-stories/employee-led-groups-assist-university-in-recruitment-retention/">
               Employee Resource Groups assist in diversity recruitment, retention
              </a>
             </h2>
             <div class="meta">
              <p class="publish-info">
               <time class="pubdate" datetime="2019-01-06T00:00:00-05:00">
                <b>
                 Published:
                </b>
                January 06, 2019
               </time>
              </p>
              <p class="author">
               <b>
                <a href="/our-stories/authors/cidni-sanders/">
                 Cidni Sanders
                </a>
               </b>
              </p>
             </div>
            </header>
            <div class="excerpt entry-summary">
             Employee resource groups (ERGs) are voluntary, employee-led groups created by a shared characteristic, interest or life experience. Seven groups currently exist at Notre Dame: Adelante Hispanos, the Black Faculty and Staff Association, Notre Dame Staff of International Descent, Notre Dame Veterans Association, SPECTRUM (LGBTQ), THRIVE! Inspiring ND Women and Young Leaders of Notre Dame.
             <p class="more-p">
              <a class="more" href="/our-stories/employee-led-groups-assist-university-in-recruitment-retention/" title="Employee Resource Groups assist in diversity recruitment, retention">
               Read More
              </a>
             </p>
